text.tspan: Economic complexity rank vs. GDP per capita, 2016
Economic complexity corresponds to ranking in the Economic Complexity Index (ECI). The ECI ranking orders
countries from the most to the least economically complex. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation (at 2011
international prices) and accounts for differences in purchasing power.
ECI Ranking (lower values imply more complexity)
Source: ECI OEC (2016), GDP per capita PPP 2011 – WDI (2017)
